'''''Ethics: Origin and Development''''' is a book by [[Peter Kropotkin]], published posthumously in 1921. It continues the argument of ''[[Mutual Aid (book)|Mutual Aid]]'', that sociable morality is essential to human survival. It was translated into English by Louis S. Friedland and Joseph R. Piroshnikoff in 1924.

